cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL. 

This paper is about grammatical error correction (GEC) using unsupervised techniques based on statistical machine translation. The paper focuses on using a pseudo learner corpus created by Google Translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to create the synthetic comparable corpus, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions using deep learning techniques, which could fall under cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
